mindmap
  root((AI Opportunity Identification))
    Use Case Viability
      Clear Business Problem
        - Visible pain point or gap
        - Defined current and future state
      Data Readiness
        - Accessible and usable data
        - Quality enables experimentation
      Pattern-Rich Decisions
        - Repetitive and scalable
        - Volume justifies investment
      Strategic Alignment
        - Supports business objectives
        - Executive sponsorship secured
    Discovery Sources
      Business Unit Pain Points
        - Manual workflows and workarounds
        - Frontline friction signals
      Customer Friction Zones
        - Journey drop-off points
        - Experience gaps and delays
      Operational Inefficiencies
        - Supply chain and scheduling
        - Forecasting and utilization gaps
      Strategic Mandates
        - CEO and board priorities
        - Transformation objectives
    Evaluation Framework
      Six Scoring Dimensions
        - Strategic value
        - Technical feasibility
        - Data readiness
        - Time to impact
        - Adoption risk
        - ROI potential
      Prioritization Matrix
        - High value and high feasibility - fund now
        - High value and low feasibility - incubate
        - Low value and high feasibility - resist
        - Low value and low feasibility - eliminate
    Pipeline Management
      Intake
        - Standardized and open
        - Guided questions reduce noise
      Evaluation
        - Cross-functional scoring
        - Structured experiments
      Prototyping
        - Minimal viable model
        - Learning over perfection
      Rollout
        - Integration and training
        - Governance and monitoring
      Feedback
        - Reassess and rescore
        - Living portfolio management
    Hype Resistance
      Vendor-Driven AI
        - Value chain integration test
        - Governance alignment check
      Over-Modeling
        - Right-size the solution
        - Rules before neural networks
      Shiny Object Syndrome
        - Problem first not tech first
        - Guardrails before deployment
    Collaborative Discovery
      Domain Experts
        - Workflow nuance and intuition
        - Translate possibility to truth
      Front Line Engagement
        - Where effort is wasted
        - Close the feedback loop
      Shared Language
        - Bridge business and technical
        - Templates and frameworks
      Co-Ownership
        - Business functions own use cases
        - Joint success criteria